text.tspan: THE PROBLEM
Through a website analysis it is clear that the foundation is passionate
about helping the community of Payatas, however the primary goal and
purpose of the charity is unclear. The UX writing within the homepage has
lots of one-liners that may sound poetic but have no relevance or context
to the user.
While there are issues with the information architecture and legibility of
some of the text, two of the most pressing issues are the absence of any
visual identity or logo which gives the appearance that the charity is
untrustworthy.
After analysing the website we had a better understanding of the current
user issues. The UX hypothesis was that firstly the messaging on the
website didnt underpin the scope of the charity or the functional aspects
of what the charity does. Secondly, the information architecture is a little
confusing and lacks clarity and cohesiveness.
Usability tests were performed to test the hypothesis. The results showed
that users were in fact unable to clearly and easily identify what the charity
does. We also found that users experienced many issues navigating
through the site and were not able to easily complete important tasks like
donating or volunteering.
The overarching goal is to increase donations and number of volunteers.
The original website had one-time donations only which limited Fairplays
revenue.
